We can represent atoms by listing the number of protons, neutrons, and electrons---for example, 2p\textsuperscript{+}, 2n\textsuperscript{0} , 2e\textsuperscript{-} for helium. Which of the following represents the \textsuperscript{18}O isotope of oxygen, given oxygen has an atomic number of 8?
(A) 7p\textsuperscript{+}, 2n\textsuperscript{0} , 9e\textsuperscript{-}
(B) 8p\textsuperscript{+}, 10n\textsuperscript{0} , 8e\textsuperscript{-}
(C) 9p\textsuperscript{+}, 9n\textsuperscript{0} , 9e\textsuperscript{-}
(D) 10p\textsuperscript{+}, 8n\textsuperscript{0} , 9e\textsuperscript{-}

Find the value of~$\left( \dfrac{1\cdot3}{2\cdot2}\right)\left( \dfrac{2\cdot4}{3\cdot3}\right)\left( \dfrac{3\cdot5}{4\cdot4}\right)\cdot\cdot\cdot\left( \dfrac{97\cdot99}{98\cdot98}\right)\left( \dfrac{98\cdot100}{99\cdot99}\right)$?
(A) \dfrac{1}{2}
(B) \dfrac{50}{99}
(C) \dfrac{9800}{9801}
(D) \dfrac{100}{99}
(E) 50

A moon of Jupiter has a nearly circular orbit of radius R and an orbit period of T. Which of the following expressions gives the mass of Jupiter?  $\textasciitilde$  $\textasciitilde$  $\textasciitilde$
(A) \dfrac{4\pi^{2}R}{T^{2}}
(B) \dfrac{2\pi R^{3}}{(GT^{2})}
(C) \dfrac{4\pi R^{2}}{(GT^{2})}
(D) \dfrac{4\pi^{2} R^{3}}{(GT^{2})}

A simple pendulum swings about the vertical equilibrium position with a maximum angular displacement of $$5^{\circ} $$ and period T. If the same pendulum is given a maximum angular displacement of $$ 10^{\circ} $$, then which of the following best gives the period of the oscillations?  $\textasciitilde$  $\textasciitilde$
(A) \frac{T}{2}
(B) \frac{T}{\sqrt{2}}
(C) T
(D) 2T
